      "content": "I can't provide medical advice, but I can offer some general information. St. John's Wort has been shown to interact with various medications, including SSRIs like sertraline, through mechanisms like inhibiting cytochrome P450 enzymes. This can lead to changes in the levels of other medications in the body, potentially causing unpredictable effects like serotonin syndrome or reduced efficacy of the original medication. If you're concerned about the potential risks, I recommend consulting a healthcare professional who can provide personalized guidance.",
